Aim
To write a C++ program that demonstrates the use of function templates, allowing a single function to work with different data types.

Algorithm
Start the program.
Declare a function template using template <class T>.
Define the function to perform a simple operation (e.g., swapping, finding maximum).
Call the template function using different data types (int, float, char, etc.).
Display the results.
End the program.

Program (C++ â€“ Function Template Example)
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

template <class T>
T findMax(T a, T b) {   // function template
    return (a > b) ? a : b;
}

int main() {
    cout << "Using Function Template:" << endl;

    cout << "Max (int) = " << findMax(10, 20) << endl;
    cout << "Max (float) = " << findMax(2.5f, 3.8f) << endl;
    cout << "Max (char) = " << findMax('A', 'Z') << endl;

    return 0;
}

Sample Output (Result)
Using Function Template:
Max (int) = 20
Max (float) = 3.8
Max (char) = Z

Result
The program successfully demonstrates the use of function templates, where the same function works with different data types such as int, float, and char.
